            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>"Home Manufactures"</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Importance of manufactures to growth of towns like Staunton,
                    Charlottesville, Lexington &amp; Harrisonburg. Look to household
                    manufacturing, since it requires very little capital. Would be good for VA since
                    it would lessen reliance on Northern goods. State should encourage this through
                    tax breaks</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Snowed Up</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Experience has satisfied us that we can do without Richmond, but haow
                    Richmond can survive the loss of communication with Staunton for an entire week,
                    we cannot imagine.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Report on 1/18 snowstorm and aftereffects. No mail from Richmond for a
                    week, no state or national news, sleighing in the streets, record
                cold.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Important Intelligence--"News from the Trains"--Sufferings of Two Citizens of
                    Staunton</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Imboden</ln>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>McCue</ln>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Report of a Rockingham County man stuck on the train in the snowstorm with
                    Imboden and McCue; his decision to leave the train at Louyisa and walk to
                    Charlottesville because there was no food left after 3 days. Travellers forced
                    to kill a stray bull and eat it frozen.</summary>
            </div>
